<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 5: ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT
        ASSEMBLY, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - INSTALLATION - TAPPETS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="connect" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TAPPETS</title>
        <para>If roller tappets are re-usable, lubricate roller tappets and guides with clean engine oil. Install into
            their original bores, unless new tappets are used (
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk document="e160_131.xml" xrefid="ef1600534">5.34</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            ).
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>
                    <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                    the tappet rollers all turn in the same direction as when removed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
